      • run

        public void run()
        the run() method of the thread, loops continuously, looking for a task in the hot local queue (unsynchronized op); if there is at least one, picks up the first one and executes it; else looks for a task in the global shared queue (synchronized op/non-blocking); if it cannot find one it checks its cold local queue (unsynchronized op), and if there is none, then goes waiting for a task from the global queue (synchronized op/blocking). Any exceptions the task throws are caught & ignored. If the data that arrives is a PoissonPill3, the thread exits its run() loop, without any regard to the tasks in its local queue.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        Overrides:
        run in class java.lang.Thread
